                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The First Committee of the United Nations General Assembly met on Monday,
                    December 18, from 10:45 a. m. to 12:40 p. m. and approved by a vote of 50 to 5,
                    with 4 abstentions, a proposal to adjourn until the three-member Group on
                    Cease-fire in Korea was able to submit a report; for the record, see U.N.
                    document A/C.1/SR.418. This was the last meeting of the committee in 1950, as
                    the report of the Entezam Group was submitted on January 2, 1951; see U.N.
                    document A/C.1/643.</p>
            </div>
